-- Clarke Hits 251 Not Out Against India in Test Vs. India, Ponting Makes 134
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-01-04T06:34:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/clarke-hits-251-not-out-against-india-in-test-vs-india-ponting-makes-134.html
Australia  captain  Michael Clarke  hit
a career-best 251 not out and  Ricky Ponting  scored 134 to lift
their team to a 291-run first-innings lead over  India  on day two
of the second cricket Test in Sydney.  Australia was 482-4 at stumps, with  Mike Hussey  the other
not out batsman on 55.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  